The paper discusses a new graph partitioning algorithm for graph database management systems that takes into account a query workload of graph pattern expressions along with their relative frequencies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of databases (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
